
[1]tuft

   TUFT, n.

   1. A collection of small things in a knot or bunch; as a tuft of
   flowers; a tuft of feathers; a tuft of grass or hair. A tuft of
   feathers forms the crest of a bird..

   2. A cluster, a clump; as a tuft of trees; a tuft of olives.

   3. In botany, a head of flowers, each elevated on a partial stalk, and
   all forming together a dense roundish mass. The word is sometimes
   applied to other collections, as little bundles of leaves, hairs and
   the like.

                     TUFT, v.t. To separate into tufts.

   1. To adorn with tufts or with a tuft.
